{"lemma":"زَوْرَة","slug":"زَوْرَة","root":"ز.#.ر","root_slug":"ز-_-ر","root_link":"/words/roots/ز-_-ر","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":false},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n18377","n18392"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B2%D9%8E%D9%88%D9%92%D8%B1%D9%8E%D8%A9"}},"translations":null,"definition":null,"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n18377","headword_ar":"زوّرهُ","root":"zwr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (A, K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tazowiyrN","text_ar":"تَزْوِيرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He honoured him;"},{"kind":"text","text":"namely, a visiter;"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"treated him with honour,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hospitality;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"made account of his visit;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"treated him well, and acknowledged his right as a visiter;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"slaughtered for him, and treated him with honour"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hospitality."},{"kind":"text","text":"(AZ.)       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zw~r Al$~ahaAdapa","text_ar":"زوّر الشَّهَادَةَ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He annulled the testimony;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"impugned and annulled it."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b2-  El-Kattál says,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"wanaHonu A^unaAsN EuwdunaA Euwdu naboEapK\n                      \n                     \n                        SaliybN wafynaA qasowapN laA tuzaw~aru"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And we are men whose wood"},{"kind":"text","text":"of which our bows are made"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"is hard wood of a neb'ah, and in us is hardiness not to be impugned and denied"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: Aboo- 'Adnán says, [perhaps reading"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nuzaw~aru","text_ar":"نُزَوَّرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which may be the correct reading,] that he means, we are not to be calumniated, because of our hardness, or hardiness, nor to be held weak. (TA.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zw~r nafosahu","text_ar":"زوّر نَفْسَهُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He stigmatized himself by the imputation of falsehood."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) [See also other explanations, below.] ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zw~r kalaAmahu","text_ar":"زوّر كَلَامَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He falsified his speech; he embellished his speech with lies;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zaxorafahu","text_ar":"زَخْرَفَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Msb.) [See also below.] ―         -b5-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zw~r Alka*iba","text_ar":"زوّر الكَذِبَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tazowiyrN","text_ar":"تَزْوِيرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S,) (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He embellished the lie."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K, TA.) ―         -b6-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zw~r $ayoy^FA","text_ar":"زوّر شَيْيًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He removed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"did away with, the obliquity of a thing;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he rectified, adjusted,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"corrected, it;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, S, Msb, K;) whether good or evil; (IAar, Msb;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he beautified,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"embellished, it."},{"kind":"text","text":"(AZ, S, K.) ―         -b7-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zw~r kalaAmFA","text_ar":"زوّر كَلَامًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He made speech right and sound,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(As,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"prepared it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(As, Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and measured it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(As,)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiY nafosihi","text_ar":"فِى نَفْسِهِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in his mind,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"before he uttered it:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(As:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he rectified, adjusted,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"corrected, it;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"beautified,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"embellished, it;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tzw~rhu","text_ar":"تزوّرهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", occurring in a verse of Nasr. Ibn-Seiyár. (TA.) And [in like manner]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zw~r AlHadiyva","text_ar":"زوّر الحَدِيثَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He rectified,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"corrected, the story, narrative,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tradition, removing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"doing away with, its obliquity:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tzw~rhu","text_ar":"تزوّرهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he did so"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ziw~rhu","text_ar":"زِوّرهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to himself."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A.) ―         -b8-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raHima A@ll~`hu A@moraA^F zaw~ara nafosahu EalaY nafosihi","text_ar":"رَحِمَ ا@للّٰهُ ا@مْرَاً زَوَّرَ نَفْسَهُ عَلَى نَفْسِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", a saying of El-Hajjáj,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"May God have mercy upon a man who rectifies,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"corrects, himself, against himself:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, * TA:) or, as some say,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who stigmatizes himself by the charge of falsehood against himself:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who accuses himself against himself:"},{"kind":"text","text":"like as you say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^anaA A^uzaw~iruka EalaY nafosika","text_ar":"اَنَا اُزَوِّرُكَ عَلَى نَفْسِكَ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I accuse thee"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of wrong"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"against thyself."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)       -A3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tazowiyrN","text_ar":"تَزْوِيرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is also syn. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ta$obiyhN","text_ar":"تَشْبِيهٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"likening"},{"kind":"text","text":"a thing to another thing; &c.]. (TA.)       -A4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zw~r","text_ar":"زوّر"},{"kind":"text","text":"said of a bird, inf. n. as above,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"His crop"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HawoSalatuhu","text_ar":"حَوْصَلَتُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became high:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(AZ, TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became full."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)"}],"source_refs":["A","K","S","As","Msb","AZ","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n18392","headword_ar":"زَوْرَةٌ","root":"zwr","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A single visit."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, TA.)       -A2-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Distance; remoteness:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K:) from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlAizowiraAru","text_ar":"الاِزْوِرَارُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S.) A poet (Sakhr El-Ghei, TA) says,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"wamaA='K waradotu EalaY zaworapK"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"To many a water have I come, notwithstanding"},{"kind":"text","text":"its"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"distance"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (S:) or, accord. to AA,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EalaY zaworapK","text_ar":"عَلَى زَوْرَةٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in this ex., accord. to one relation"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zuwrap","text_ar":"زُورَة"},{"kind":"text","text":", but the former is the better known, means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"upon a she-camel that looked from the outer angle of her eye, by reason of her vehemence and sharpness of temper."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)"}],"source_refs":["S","K"]}]}}